Confirmed BROKEN on Vista/Windows 7 x64. Come on guys, x64 has been out what? Five years now starting with XP?

FOR x64 PEOPLE:

You need to find CorFlags.exe program, i think that it's part of Windows SDK.

When you have it execute it with following parametars:
CorFlags.exe /32BIT+ ""

this will force MIK to run in 32 mode

FOR x64 PEOPLE:

You need to find CorFlags.exe program, i think that it's part of Windows SDK.

When you have it execute it with following parametars:
CorFlags.exe /32BIT+ "path_to_MixedInKey.exe"

this will force MIK to run in 32 mode
